#Logistics Company Join Analysis (Part 2)

This project demonstrates SQL-based analysis of a logistics dataset using multiple JOIN types to answer real-world business questions around data completeness, shipment filtering, and customer segmentation.

The analysis focuses on understanding how different JOIN types impact query results and business insights.

--

#Objective

The primary goals of this analysis were to:

-Compare different SQL JOIN types (FULL, LEFT, RIGHT)
-Analyze how data is retained or excluded across tables
-Identify shipment characteristics based on weight
-Segment customers based on location data
-Strengthen SQL skills using advanced JOIN logic

#Business Questions

-How can we view all customers and all shipments together?
-Which shipments meet specific weight requirements?
-Which customers are located in Texas?
-How do different JOIN types affect the results returned?
-When should each JOIN type be used in real-world analysis?
