#SQL Analysis

-1. All Customers and All Shipments (FULL JOIN)
SELECT customers.customer_name,
       shipments.package_description
FROM customers
FULL JOIN shipments
    ON customers.customer_id = shipments.customer_id;

Business Insight:
Combines all customer and shipment data, including unmatched records from both tables.

Business Impact:
Useful for data audits, identifying missing relationships, and ensuring dataset completeness.

-2. Shipments Weighing 3kg or More (RIGHT JOIN)
SELECT shipments.shipment_id,
       customers.shipping_address,
       shipments.weight_kg
FROM customers
RIGHT JOIN shipments
    ON customers.customer_id = shipments.customer_id
WHERE shipments.weight_kg >= 3
ORDER BY shipments.weight_kg DESC;

Business Insight:
Identifies heavier shipments and prioritizes shipment data regardless of customer match.

Business Impact:
Supports operational planning for heavy shipments, including logistics, handling, and cost considerations.

-3. Customers in Texas (LEFT JOIN)
SELECT customers.customer_name,
       customers.billing_address,
       customers.shipping_address,
       shipments.shipment_id
FROM customers
LEFT JOIN shipments
    ON customers.customer_id = shipments.customer_id
WHERE customers.billing_address LIKE '%TX%';

Business Insight:
Identifies customers located in Texas and links them to any associated shipments.

Business Impact:
Supports regional analysis, targeted marketing, and geographic operational planning.
